It marks Sheeran's most successful song to date after a dozen runs at the chart. Sheeran's "Sing" is the first single from his forthcoming second album, and moved 124,000 copies in its first week. He's also writing and recording his second album while on tour. It's slated for release in February 2014., 4398=But how did Sheeran really become famous? It was thanks, in large part, to an open mic night he played in April 2010. Spotted at The Foxxhole by none other than Jamie Foxx, he was given blanket use of Foxx's recording studio and the run of his Hollywood home.
